2. Middleware

Middleware sits between the request and the view.
It can process the request before it reaches the view
and process the response before it goes back to the browser.

Two built-in middleware:

• SecurityMiddleware
  - Adds security headers.
  - Protects against common web attacks.

• AuthenticationMiddleware
  - Identifies the logged-in user.
  - Makes request.user available.


3. WSGI vs ASGI

WSGI
- Works synchronously.
- Handles one request at a time.
- Default server interface in Django.

ASGI
- Works asynchronously.
- Supports WebSockets.
- Suitable for chat applications,
  live notifications and real-time apps.

Django uses WSGI by default.
Use ASGI for asynchronous applications.


4. MVC vs MVT

MVC

